Introduction

    Mevenide2-Netbeans is a Netbeans plugin which integrate all the maven2 project management possibilities into Netbeans.
It allows to open any Maven project natively within the IDE without any imports.

* News:

    2008/05/07 - Version 3.1 release is out. It is available from the default stable update center of NetBeans 6.0 and 6.1
or as a {{{http://mevenide.codehaus.org/release/mevenide2-netbeans-3.1.1.zip}zip file with NBMs}}
It has a bunch of new features described in {{{http://wiki.netbeans.org/MavenBestPractices}this article}} at netbeans.org. The article also describes how to install the modules
and provides additional hints on usage. The major changes include:

        * new 2.1-SNAPSHOT maven embedder included.

        * local and remote repository indexing (using {{{http://nexus.sonatype.org}Nexus}})

        * Web frameworks support

        * Improved profiling support (aka configurations)

        * Check the {{{http://wiki.netbeans.org/MavenBestPractices}article}} for these and more features in detail.

